{
  "local_port": 59596,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I import my Gmail contacts into Skype?",
  "response": "Importing your Gmail contacts into Skype can streamline your communication by allowing you to connect with your existing contacts seamlessly. Below are two primary methods to achieve this: **Directly Connecting Your Google Account to Skype** and **Exporting Gmail Contacts and Importing Them via Outlook or Windows Contacts**.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 1: Directly Connect Your Google Account to Skype**\n\nSkype offers the ability to connect directly with your Google account, allowing you to sync your Gmail contacts effortlessly. Here\u2019s how to do it:\n\n1. **Open Skype and Sign In**\n   - Launch the Skype application on your computer or mobile device.\n   - Sign in using your Skype or Microsoft account credentials.\n\n2. **Navigate to the Contacts Section**\n   - On the desktop app, locate and click on the **\"Contacts\"** or **\"People\"** icon, usually found in the sidebar.\n   \n3. **Find the \"Find Contacts\" Option**\n   - Look for an option labeled **\"Find Contacts\"**, **\"Add Contacts\"**, or similar. This might be represented by a magnifying glass icon or located within a menu.\n\n4. **Choose to Connect Your Google Account**\n   - Among the available contact sources, select **\"Google\"** or **\"Gmail\"**.\n   - If prompted, click on **\"Connect\"** or **\"Sign In with Google\"**.\n\n5. **Sign In to Your Google Account**\n   - A new window will appear asking you to enter your Gmail credentials.\n   - Enter your email address and password associated with your Gmail account.\n\n6. **Grant Permissions**\n   - Skype will request permission to access your Google Contacts.\n   - Click **\"Allow\"** to grant the necessary permissions for Skype to access and sync your contacts.\n\n7. **Synchronize Contacts**\n   - Once connected, Skype will begin syncing your Gmail contacts.\n   - The synchronization process may take a few moments depending on the number of contacts.\n\n8. **Access Your Imported Contacts**\n   - After syncing, your Gmail contacts will appear in your Skype contacts list.\n   - You can now start chatting, calling, or video conferencing with them directly from Skype.\n\n**_Note:_** The exact labels and locations of these options might vary slightly depending on the Skype version and platform (Windows, macOS, Android, iOS) you are using. Ensure that you're using the latest version of Skype for the best experience.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 2: Export Gmail Contacts and Import via Outlook or Windows Contacts**\n\nIf the direct connection method isn\u2019t available or doesn\u2019t work as expected, you can manually export your Gmail contacts and then import them into Skype via Outlook or the Windows Contacts app.\n\n#### **Step 1: Export Your Gmail Contacts**\n\n1. **Access Google Contacts**\n   - Go to [Google Contacts](https://contacts.google.com/) and sign in with your Gmail account.\n\n2. **Select Contacts to Export**\n   - To export all contacts, simply proceed. To export specific contacts, select them by checking the boxes next to each contact.\n\n3. **Initiate Export**\n   - Click on the **\"Export\"** option, which may be found under the **\"More\"** dropdown menu (represented by three vertical dots).\n\n4. **Choose Export Format**\n   - Select **\"Outlook CSV\"** or **\"Google CSV\"** format depending on what you plan to use for importing.\n   - Click **\"Export\"** to download the CSV file to your computer.\n\n#### **Step 2: Import Contacts into Outlook or Windows Contacts**\n\n**_Option A: Using Microsoft Outlook_**\n\n1. **Open Microsoft Outlook**\n   - Launch Outlook on your computer.\n\n2. **Navigate to the Import Feature**\n   - Go to **\"File\"** > **\"Open & Export\"** > **\"Import/Export\"**.\n\n3. **Choose Import Action**\n   - Select **\"Import from another program or file\"** and click **\"Next\"**.\n\n4. **Select File Type**\n   - Choose **\"Comma Separated Values\" (CSV)** and click **\"Next\"**.\n\n5. **Choose the CSV File**\n   - Browse to the location where you saved the exported Gmail contacts CSV file.\n   - Select the file and choose how you want duplicates to be handled, then click **\"Next\"**.\n\n6. **Select Destination Folder**\n   - Choose the **\"Contacts\"** folder where you want the imported contacts to appear.\n   - Click **\"Finish\"** to start the import process.\n\n**_Option B: Using Windows Contacts (Windows 10/11)_**\n\n1. **Open the Contacts App**\n   - Press **`Win + S`**, type **\"Contacts\"**, and open the **\"Contacts\"** app.\n\n2. **Import Contacts**\n   - Click on **\"Manage\"** and then select **\"Import Contacts\"**.\n\n3. **Choose the CSV File**\n   - Browse to and select the CSV file you exported from Gmail.\n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to map any fields if prompted and complete the import.\n\n#### **Step 3: Sync Imported Contacts with Skype**\n\n1. **Open Skype**\n   - Launch the Skype application and sign in.\n\n2. **Access Contact Settings**\n   - Click on your profile picture or the **\"Settings\"** icon.\n\n3. **Find Contact Sync Options**\n   - Navigate to **\"Contacts\"**, **\"Manage Contacts\"**, or a similar section within settings.\n\n4. **Enable Contact Syncing**\n   - Ensure that Skype is set to sync with Outlook or Windows Contacts, depending on where you imported your Gmail contacts.\n   - There might be an option like **\"Sync contacts with Outlook\"** or **\"Sync with Windows\"**. Enable it.\n\n5. **Complete the Sync**\n   - Skype will now sync the contacts from Outlook or Windows Contacts into your Skype account.\n   - This process may take a few minutes based on the number of contacts.\n\n6. **Verify Imported Contacts**\n   - Once syncing is complete, check your Skype contacts list to ensure that your Gmail contacts have been successfully imported.\n\n**_Note:_** If you\u2019re using a Mac or if Skype doesn\u2019t provide direct syncing options, you might need to manually add contacts or use intermediary services/apps that support both platforms.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n\n- **Regular Syncing:** If you frequently update your Gmail contacts, consider setting up a regular sync (if supported) to keep your Skype contacts up-to-date automatically.\n  \n- **Privacy Considerations:** Always ensure you\u2019re comfortable with the permissions you grant when connecting accounts. Skype will have access to your Gmail contacts if you use the direct connection method.\n\n- **Support and Help:** If you encounter issues during the process, refer to Skype\u2019s [official support page](https://support.skype.com/) or Google\u2019s [Contacts Help](https://support.google.com/contacts/) for additional assistance.\n\n---\n\nBy following either of these methods, you should be able to successfully import your Gmail contacts into Skype, enhancing your communication capabilities across both platforms.",
